Rating: 3
I like these, but they won't permanently replace my America's Test Kitchen chocolate chip cookies. They did turn out well using bittersweet chocolate for the grated; yes, definitely grate the chocolate in the food processor, and add a bit of the oatmeal and flour so that the chocolate does not start to stick to itself as the friction of the blade heats it up. I left all the proportions as written. 15 minutes at 325 yielded a great texture, once the cookies cooled. They look pale and underdone, but set up just right. Perfect for dunking in cold milk. I'm going to try the suggestion of a sprinkle of sea salt on the last batch. Hubby thought they were a little bland, despite all the chocolate. Maybe a bit of cinnamon or chili next time? Hmmm. The peanut flavor is not pronounced, but I always think peanut butter cookies taste better the next day; the proof will be in tomorrow's lunch. Final note: I got 85 cookies out of this batter, using big rounded tablespoons. Generously sized, when baked.

