I've now made 3 versions of this cookie, all with one batter. I did process a cup of the oats, and I did use the grated chocolate (I used bittersweet, tho). I think those 2 steps are critical to making this cookie special. Taking some tips from others, I increased the PB (natural, peanuts only) to 1 cup; decreased sugars to 3/4 cup each; decreased butter to 1/2 cup and made up the difference with 1/4 cup applesauce and the additional 1/4 cup PB. I baked some of the dough in an 8x8 pan for bars which I did not care for - soft and chewy - if you like that, you would like the bars. Then I baked some cookies at 325 until pale golden. Excellent cookie, but too soft for me. I then baked some at 350 until light brown, and those were PERFECT. Nice crisp texture on the outside, moist inside.

