These cookies were so good! Everyone that I gave a cookie to, loved it!! Like one other reader, I did not use the grated chocolate in the recipe. The chocolate chips are enough. I think I'll experiment next time. Maybe not grind so much of the oatmeal so they are a little chunkier. And possibly add chopped walnuts!

Rating: 4
Another note is that this recipe freezes very well--a good thing because one batch makes a ton of cookies. I squish it into logs and double wrap in aluminum foil. Makes an excellent gift for those who love home-baked cookies, and much better than store-bought slice-n-bake. The only problem is that most of the dough in my house gets eaten frozen and never makes it to the oven.

